The paper deals with the issue of determining trust of data available in the Semantic Web, which is a fundamental problem in database systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Database). The paper also proposes an approach based on the translation of SPARQL into relational queries, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the issue of non-monotonic constructs, which is related to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a solution to a problem in the literature, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE).
